National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: Albuquerque, NM
Accident Number: CEN17CA013
Date & Time: 10/02/2016, 0830 MDT
Registration: N5161Y
Aircraft: AEROSTAR RX-8
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event: Collision during takeoff/land
Injuries: 2 Minor, 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis The hot air free balloon was participating in the Albuquerque International Balloon Fiesta.
According to the pilot, he was approaching a vacant field for landing after a one-hour flight.
The pilot approached the field from about 8 feet above the ground and the envelope impacted an unnoticed power line during landing.
The pilot deflated the envelope, but the wind pulled the envelope and basket into the lines, which resulted in arcing against the uprights and frame.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: The pilot's improperly planned landing, which resulted in a strike with power lines.
Investigation Docket: http://dms.ntsb.gov/pubdms/search/dockList.cfm?mKey=94168
